55. nidos: nestlings. Cf. Verg. Aen. 5. 214 Cui domus et dulces latebroso in pumice nidi. l2.475 Pabula parva leqens, nidisque loquacibus escas. Georq. 4.17 Ore serunt dulcem nidis immitibus escam. Ov. Medic. 77 Addita de querulo volucrum medicamina nido. Seu. Herc. Fur. 148—9 querulos inter nidos Thracia paelex.

culmine: the top of a tree. Cf. Stat. Theb. 7. 800 iam frondea nutant culmina and Sil. 5. 514 (Vulcanus aesculi) culmina torret.

56. Pensal: cf. Ov. Epist. 2. 143 Stat nece malura tenerum pensare pudorem. amore: i. e. her love for her young.

alitura: the author shows marked fondness for the future participle, cf. cessurus, 45, and peritura, 74 and 87.

querellas: used here with reference to the story of Philomela's meta- morphosis, as also in Verg. Georq. 4. 511—2 Qualis populea maerens Philomela sub umbra Amissos queritur fetus. Hor. Carm. 4. 12. 5—6 N idum ponit Ityn flebiliter qemens Infelix avis. Ov. Fast. 4. 481—2 Quaecumque ingreditur miseris loca cuncta querellis Implet, ut amissum cum qemil ales Ityn. Querella and the related words, however, are often used of the song of birds in general. Cf. querulos, 55, and Hor. Epod. 2. 26 Queruntur in silvis aves. Ov. Am. 3. 1. 4 Et latere ex omn-i dulce querunter aves.
